body.p:
The Jarſeys are under the ſame Circumſtances with your ſelves, in reſpect of their Charter, yet have willingly ſubmitted to the Kings pleaſure and Right of the Millitia, who are commanded by his Excellency; 
                        〈◊〉
                      the Governour of that Collony acts there without the leaſt interruption: He calls Aſſemblies, makes Laws, raiſes Money, ordains and keeps Courts, only commands the Militia under his Excellency, who has not altered one ſingle Officer in that Collony.
